{"section": "3.8.2: The components of an inductive proof.", "qid": 0, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n </p>\n <p>\n  <b>\n   Theorem:\n  </b>\n  For all n \u2208\n  <b>\n   Z\n  </b>\n  <sup>\n   +\n  </sup>\n  , Q(n) is true,\n  <br/>\n  <br/>\n  where Q(n) is a statement that is parameterized by a positive integer n.\n </p>\n <p>\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   1)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   In an inductive proof of the theorem, what must be proven in the base case?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember97\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"Q(0) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember96&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    Q(0) is true\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember99\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"Q(1) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember98&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    Q(1) is true\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember101\">\n   <input aria-label=\"Q(k) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember100&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    Q(k) is true\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember103\">\n   <input aria-label=\"Q(n) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember102&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    Q(n) is true\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember97\">\n <input aria-label=\"Q(0) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember96&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  Q(0) is true\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember99\">\n <input aria-label=\"Q(1) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember98&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  Q(1) is true\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember101\">\n <input aria-label=\"Q(k) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember100&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  Q(k) is true\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember103\">\n <input aria-label=\"Q(n) is true\" name=\"21\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember102&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  Q(n) is true\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "Q(1) is true", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n The first positive integer is\n <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n  n = 1\n </span>\n , so the base case shows that Q(n) is true for\n <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n  n = 1\n </span>\n .\n</div>\n"}